Package ohos.wifi

Class WifiEvents

  • java.lang.Object
    • ohos.wifi.WifiEvents

  • public final class WifiEvents
extends Object
    Provides parameters for Wi-Fi interfaces.

    The parameters include Wi-Fi broadcasting status and common Wi-Fi parameters.

    Since:
    3

      • EVENT_ACTIVE_STATE

        public static final String EVENT_ACTIVE_STATE
        Indicates the action of a common event about the Wi-Fi state, such as enabled and disabled. You can register this common event to listen for Wi-Fi state changes.

        In this common event sent to you, the PARAM_ACTIVE_STATE key of the IntentParams key-value pair carries specific information about the Wi-Fi state change, and the value can be STATE_ACTIVE (Wi-Fi disabled) or STATE_INACTIVE (Wi-Fi enabled).

        Since:
        3
        See Also:
        PARAM_ACTIVE_STATE, STATE_ACTIVE, STATE_INACTIVE, Constant Field Values

      • EVENT_CONN_STATE

        public static final String EVENT_CONN_STATE
        Indicates the action of a common event that the Wi-Fi connection state has changed. You can register this common event to listen for Wi-Fi connection state changes.

        In this common event sent to you, the PARAM_CONN_STATE key of the IntentParams key-value pair carries specific information about the Wi-Fi connection state change, and the value can be STATE_DISCONNECTED (Wi-Fi disconnected) or STATE_CONNECTED (Wi-Fi connected).

        Since:
        3
        See Also:
        PARAM_CONN_STATE, STATE_DISCONNECTED, STATE_CONNECTED, Constant Field Values

        In this common event sent to you, the PARAM_HOTSPOT_STATE key of the IntentParams key-value pair carries specific information about the Wi-Fi hotspot state change, and the value can be STATE_HOTSPOT_INACTIVE (Wi-Fi hotspot disabled) or STATE_HOTSPOT_ACTIVE (Wi-Fi hotspot enabled).

      • EVENT_HOTSPOT_STATION_JOIN

        public static final String EVENT_HOTSPOT_STATION_JOIN
        Indicates the action of a common event that a client has joined the Wi-Fi hotspot of the current device. You can register this common event to listen for information about the clients joining your hotspot.

        In this common event sent to you, the keys of the IntentParams key-value pair carry the following information:

        To subscribe to this common event, your application must have the ohos.permission.GET_WIFI_INFO permission.

        Since:
        3
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

        In this common event sent to you, the keys of the IntentParams key-value pair carry the following information:

        To subscribe to this common event, your application must have the ohos.permission.GET_WIFI_INFO permission.

      • EVENT_P2P_CONN_STATE_CHANGED

        public static final String EVENT_P2P_CONN_STATE_CHANGED
        Indicates the event that the state of the Wi-Fi P2P connection has changed. You can register this event to listen for state changes of the Wi-Fi P2P connection.

        When receiving a broadcast of a Wi-Fi P2P information change, you can call WifiP2pController.requestP2pInfo(int, WifiP2pCallback) to request the Wi-Fi P2P information.

        Since:
        3
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • EVENT_P2P_CURRENT_DEVICE_STATE_CHANGED

        public static final String EVENT_P2P_CURRENT_DEVICE_STATE_CHANGED
        Indicates the event that the state of the current device has changed. You can register this event to listen for state changes of the current device.

        When receiving a broadcast of a state change for the current device, you can call WifiP2pController.requestP2pInfo(int, WifiP2pCallback) to request information about the current device.

        Since:
        3
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • EVENT_P2P_DEVICES_CHANGED

        public static final String EVENT_P2P_DEVICES_CHANGED
        Indicates the event that the state of peer devices has changed. You can register this event to listen for state changes of peer devices.

        When receiving a broadcast of a change in the peer device list, you can call WifiP2pController.requestP2pInfo(int, WifiP2pCallback) to request information about the peer device list.

        Since:
        3
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • EVENT_P2P_DEVICES_DISCOVERY_STATE

        public static final String EVENT_P2P_DEVICES_DISCOVERY_STATE
        Indicates the event that the state of Wi-Fi P2P discovery has changed. You can register this event to listen for state changes of Wi-Fi P2P discovery.

        In this event, the PARAM_P2P_DISCOVERY key of the IntentParams key-value pair carries information about the Wi-Fi P2P discovery state after the change, and the value can be PEERS_P2P_DISCOVERY_OFF (Wi-Fi P2P discovery is disabled) or PEERS_P2P_DISCOVERY_ON (Wi-Fi P2P discovery is enabled).

        Since:
        3
        See Also:
        PARAM_P2P_DISCOVERY, PEERS_P2P_DISCOVERY_OFF, PEERS_P2P_DISCOVERY_ON, Constant Field Values

      • EVENT_P2P_STATE_CHANGED

        public static final String EVENT_P2P_STATE_CHANGED
        Indicates the event that the state of Wi-Fi P2P has changed. You can register this event to listen for Wi-Fi P2P state changes.

        In this event, the PARAM_P2P_STATE_CHANGED key of the IntentParams key-value pair carries information about the Wi-Fi P2P state change, and the value can be STATE_P2P_OFF (Wi-Fi P2P is disabled) or STATE_P2P_ON (Wi-Fi P2P is enabled).

        Since:
        3
        See Also:
        PARAM_P2P_STATE_CHANGED, STATE_P2P_OFF, STATE_P2P_ON, Constant Field Values

      • EVENT_RSSI_VALUE

        public static final String EVENT_RSSI_VALUE
        Indicates the action of a common event that the Wi-Fi signal strength (RSSI) has changed. You can register this common event to listen for Wi-Fi RSSI changes of the connected network.

        In this common event sent to you, the PARAM_RSSI_VALUE key of the IntentParams key-value pair is associated with a specific value of the new RSSI.

        To subscribe to this common event, your application must have the ohos.permission.GET_WIFI_INFO permission.

        Since:
        3
        See Also:
        PARAM_RSSI_VALUE, Constant Field Values

      • EVENT_SCAN_STATE

        public static final String EVENT_SCAN_STATE
        Indicates the action of a common event that the Wi-Fi access point has been scanned and proven to be available. You can register this common event to listen for the Wi-Fi scanning result.

        In this common event sent to you, the PARAM_SCAN_STATE key of the IntentParams key-value pair carries specific information about the Wi-Fi scanning result, and the value can be STATE_SCAN_FAIL (scanning failed) or STATE_SCAN_SUCCESS (scanning succeeded).

        To subscribe to this common event, your application must have the ohos.permission.LOCATION permission.

        Since:
        3
        See Also:
        PARAM_SCAN_STATE, STATE_SCAN_FAIL, STATE_SCAN_SUCCESS, Constant Field Values
